## Install

```bash
npm install --save {{packageName}}
```

## Usage

### Basic

```typescript
import {{{parserName}}} from '{{{packageName}}}'

const parser = new {{{parserName}}}()

parser.parse('source Markdown content')

parser.parse('source Markdown content', {
  shouldReservePosition: true,
})

// Iterable source chunks are concatenated during parsing.
parser.parse(['source ', 'chunks'])
```

### Generator input

```typescript
import {{{parserName}}} from '{{{packageName}}}'

const parser = new {{{parserName}}}()

function* source() {
  yield 'hello '
  yield 'world'
}

parser.parse(source())
```

### Constructor options

| Name                      | Type                       | Required | Default              | Description                              |
| :------------------------ | :------------------------- | :------- | :------------------- | :--------------------------------------- |
| `blockFallbackTokenizer`  | `IBlockFallbackTokenizer`  | No       | `ParagraphTokenizer` | Fallback for unmatched block content     |
| `inlineFallbackTokenizer` | `IInlineFallbackTokenizer` | No       | `TextTokenizer`      | Fallback for unmatched inline content    |
| `defaultParseOptions`     | `IParseOptions`            | No       | See below            | Default options for every `parse()` call |

### `IParseOptions`

| Name                        | Type                      | Required | Default                 | Description                                    |
| :-------------------------- | :------------------------ | :------- | :---------------------- | :--------------------------------------------- |
| `shouldReservePosition`     | `boolean`                 | No       | `false`                 | Include source positions in generated nodes    |
| `presetDefinitions`         | `Association[]`           | No       | `[]`                    | Preset link-reference identifiers              |
| `presetFootnoteDefinitions` | `Association[]`           | No       | `[]`                    | Preset footnote-reference identifiers          |
| `formatUrl`                 | `(url: string) => string` | No       | `encodeLinkDestination` | Format URLs stored in generated resource nodes |
